⠀
As a chef, I know that the best dishes require the best ingredients.⠀
⠀
And as a father, I care where those ingredients come from. ⠀⠀
⠀⠀
That's why I'm so excited to announce that I'll be partnering with OurHarvest - a New York-based online farmers market that delivers high-quality, locally-sourced food right to your door.⠀
⠀
Head to @OurHarvest, where I'll be regularly sharing my favorite products, top tips and go-to recipes.⠀⠀
⠀⠀
See you there!

node.text: Remember when I told you recently...my biggest thanksgiving fail was not having enough mashed potatoes? Well here is a recipe for pommes boulangère one of my favorite ways to enjoy potatoes that pairs wonderfully with your thanksgiving meal. And since we’re two weeks you will have more than enough time to prep and practice. This recipe is actually easy and looks impressive. And while this year won’t include too many “potlucks” this dish is great because any leftovers can go right into your fridge at home. No need for Tupperware 👍 Recipe on my website. #thanksgiving #pommesboulangère #tbt @littlestar84 @socialfly

Full disclosure @littlestar84 and I recorded this a few weeks ago but in the spirit of keeping our knife skills fresh I’m sharing anyway. This one one of the most requested vegetables so be sure and save this one. Squash is so versatile and available year-round but it is best from early fall through winter. Luckily if you store in a cool dark
place it can last for at least a month. And if you had some around and wanted to grill for a summer side it could work👍 #wecook #knife #squash #butternutsquash #howto #knifeskills #seasonwithauthority @foodnetwork @korinknives @victorinoxswissarmy @hedleyandbennett

node.text: Happy Monday and happy August to everyone. August is the perfect summer month for juicy tomatoes. And I can’t believe how much you guys have asked about how to slice, dice, wedge and core these guys. So since we filmed this is July when tomatoes aren’t as juicy this time was perfect to show you how to get that “cute wedge” needed for salads etc. We will be sharing a few more “tomato skills” videos now that they are prime for picking & eating so send us your questions! 🍅🍅🍅 @littlestar84 @foodnetwork #tomato #tomatoes #knife #knifeskills #august #seasonwithauthority #wedge #wecook

node.text: "Anyway, like I was sayin', shrimp is the fruit of the sea. You can barbecue it, boil it, broil it, bake it, sauté it.” Bonus points to who knows what movie that is from 😉 Full disclosure, we filmed this in May pre haircuts 🤪 But knowing how to clean, peel and cook shrimp was highly requested from everyone! So we’re happy to share some skills. Fun fact one of @littlestar84 first jobs was at Tully’s Seafood Market in Hampton Bays where she cleaned shrimp using a deveiner. I’m using a pairing knife. Either way can work. Most importantly know where your seafood and shrimp come from. Lots of tips in the video 👍 #shrimp #peelingshrimp #knife #howto #tutorial #seasonwithauthority #wecook #seafood @foodnetwork

See you there!
